Durban - eThekwini Air pollution has issued a warning to residents living on the south of Durban to stay indoors following a factory fire that has caused low-level pollution. 
 

 According to the Department, the smoke can be hazardous and have urged residents in the Montclair, Merebank, Clairwood, Wentworth and surrounds to take cover. 

 

 At around 4:46am the fire department was called to a building that was engulfed in flames. 

 

 Jini Trading, a Chinese shoe manufacturing factory, situated in Brooklyn Road, Jacobs was engulfed in flames. 

 

 
  







